description:
This artsy space on a quiet street in Bedstuy is centrally located in the hottest Brooklyn neighborhood with nearby restaurants, coffee shops and bars. Enjoy a morning coffee on the balcony and observe a community unique to NYC. Explore the hood's brownstones or travel easy by foot, bike or public transit to bordering Williamsburg, Greenpoint, Fort Greene or Crown Heights. On the weekend check out the flea market, stoop sales and farmer's market. Manhattan is just 20-30 minutes by train.

Balcony, artwork, central Brooklyn location, quiet and uniquely Hasidic street in the heart of a diverse, vibrant, creative and hip neighborhood, while apartment or single room available.

Wifi, coffee (upon request), towels (upon request), balcony, amazing neighborhood with everything you want out of Brooklyn, bike and trains and busses, record player and nice vinyl selection.

I am around if you need me.

This neighborhood is the best because its people and culture are so diverse. Street art tributes to Biggie Smalls, Hasidic Jews, art students, families, young professionals- everyone and everything is here. There's just enough grit and just enough art. It's also so easy to get to anywhere around Brooklyn. We've got great bars, restaurants and coffee shops. My favorite Mexican restaurant is a block away. It feels like home in a big city.

Busses around each corner. Citibikes at the end of the block. 5 minute walk to the G train; 15 to the A/C. Everything you really need is within walking distance. Lots of taxis and uber. We can talk about my bike if you're interested in using it.

You can rent the whole place for a week or just the spare room for longer at a lower price. Suitable for 4 people with two full beds. There's a couch for a fifth person at an additional cost.
house_rules:
• Check in time is 9AM - 8PM
• May not be safe or suitable for children (0-12 years)
• No parties or events
• No smoking

There will be a charge for more than 2 occupants of $30 a night. Pets are considered on a case by case basis. Bike rental is available (one bike available). A cleaning fee of $30 applies. House may or may not be suitable for children.

photos.caption: Clean, charming and cozy living space.
A small humidifier and diffuser makes it even cozier in here.
The hallway shelf is good for shoes and coats.
There's a full closet and towels are available on request. The window overlooks a back yard.
The room is bright and super cozy as the sun sets.
The kitchen has any cookware you need if you want to cook, including a few spices above the stove.
The front bedroom is bright and cozy

The apartment is situated in BedStuy, just on the edge of Clinton Hill, Williamsburg, Crown Heights and Fort Greene. It's a great neighborhood for exploring or you can take the train or bus just around the corner. Williamsburg and Greenpoint are just 15 minutes away. Ian's it's just 20/30 minutes  to downtown Manhattan. I have a bike you can use too. Citibikes are also available at the end of the block.
The bathroom is bright, light and tidy. If you need toiletries, let me know.

Amazing views of Brooklyn from the balcony. This is a rare and safe Hasidic street in the heart of Bedstuy. It's great for people watching. Restaurants, grocery stores, hip coffee shops and bars are all right around the corner.  BAM and downtown Brooklyn are just a walk or an even faster bus or bike ride away. Fort Green Park is super close too. Lots of Notorious BIG murals and street art too.

review.comments: l'appartement correspond parfaitement à l'annonce, logement très cosy; Joanna est disponible, elle donne des adresses, des conseils. loin du brouhaha, de l'agitation de Manhattan, ce logement permet de découvrir les différents aspects de Brooklyn. on rejoint aussi très facilement Manhattan par le métro. excellent voyage!
